{
  "texts": [
    "The purpose of this paper is to build a foundation for such a theory.",
    "As already explained before, to study our problem we generalize the approach from [64, 78, 89].",
    "Instead of dealing with the PDE (1.5) we work directly with the \"lifted\" HJB (1.6).",
    "However, here the HJB equations (1.3) (on the Hilbert space H n) and (1.6) (on E) are infinite dimensional.",
    "Thus we face significant mathematical difficulties introduced by such intrinsic infinite dimensionality:"
  ]
}